      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "SALEM, Ore, June 21.--Articles\nof incorporation for the new coast\nrailway, known as the Independ-\nence-Siletz Pacific railway, were\nfiled with the secretary of state to-\nday by Independence capitalists. 1t\nIs capitalized at a half million.\n\n\nThe road will run from a point\nnear Simpson. Polk county. to the\nPacific coast through the Siletz In\ndian reservation. Cape Foul\nWeather, Lincoln county, will be\nthe western terminus. The incor-\nporators are o. w. Taylor, d. w.\nSears and M. Mirschberg, Independ.\nence capitalists."
    }
  ]
